12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 74 O.S. 2021, Section 78a, as
14 amended by Section 8, Chapter 199, O.S.L. 2025 (74 O.S. Supp. 2025,
15 Section 78a), is amended to read as follows:
16 Section 78a. A. State agencies with authority to own motor
17 vehicles shall submit a requisition to the Director of the Office of
18 Management and Enterprise Services prior to acquisition of a motor
19 vehicle. The requisition shall state the type of vehicle, the
20 intended purpose of the vehicle, a statement that the agency has
21 actual need for the vehicle, the supplier of the vehicle, that the
22 state agency has sufficient funds to acquire and maintain the
23 vehicle and cite the statutory authority of the state agency to
24 acquire a vehicle.
ENGR. H. B. NO. 1752 Page 1

1 B. The Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise
2 Services shall review the requisition and approve or deny the
3 request of the state agency within fifteen (15) days of receipt.
4 C. The provisions of subsections A and B of this section shall
5 not apply to the Department of Public Safety, the Commissioners of
6 the Land Office, the Attorney General's Office, the Oklahoma
7 District Attorneys Council, the Oklahoma State Bureau of Narcotics
8 and Dangerous Drugs Control or the Oklahoma Military Department.
9 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
10 Passed the House of Representatives the 11th day of March, 2026.
